    "message_2": "First, let's find the determinant of the coefficient matrix (D):\n\nD = | 2  3 -1 |\n      | 1 -2  5 |\n      | 3  4 -2 |\n\nD = 2((-2)(-2) - 5(4)) - 3(1(-2) - 5(3)) - (-1)(1(4) - 3(-2))\nD = 2(4 - 20) - 3(-2 + 15) + (4 + 6)\nD = 2(-16) - 3(13) + 10\nD = -32 - 39 + 10\nD = -61\n\nNow, let's find the determinants of the matrices with the columns replaced by the constant terms (Dx, Dy, Dz):\n\nDx = | 4  3 -1 |\n        | -3 -2  5 |\n        | 7  4 -2 |\n\nDx = 4((-2)(-2) - 5(4)) - 3(-3(-2) - 5(7)) - (-1)(-3(4) - 7(-2))\nDx = 4(4 - 20) - 3(6 - 35) + (12 + 14)\nDx = 4(-16) - 3(-29) + 26\nDx = -64 + 87 + 26\nDx = 49\n\nDy = | 2  4 -1 |\n        | 1 -3  5 |\n        | 3  7 -2 |\n\nDy = 2((-3)(-2) - 5(7)) - 4(1(-2) - 5(3)) - (-1)(1(7) - 3(-3))\nDy = 2(6 - 35) - 4(-2 + 15) + (7 + 9)\nDy = 2(-29) - 4(13) + 16\nDy = -58 - 52 + 16\nDy = -94\n\nDz = | 2  3  4 |\n        | 1 -2 -3 |\n        | 3  4  7 |\n\nDz = 2((-2)(7) - (-3)(4)) - 3(1(7) - (-3)(3)) - 4(1(4) - 3(-2))\nDz = 2(-14 + 12) - 3(7 + 9) - 4(4 + 6)\nDz = 2(-2) - 3(16) - 4(10)\nDz = -4 - 48 - 40\nDz = -92\n\nNow, we can find the values of x, y, and z:\n\nx = Dx / D = 49 / -61\ny = Dy / D = -94 / -61\nz = Dz / D = -92 / -61\n\nSo, the solution is:\n\nx = -49/61\ny = 94/61\nz = 92/61"
